   - Downloading: smoothly climbs through 5–70% as bytes arrive.
   - Extracting: steps forward as each layer completes (70–92%).
   - Recreating: jumps to ~94%.
   - Done: smoothly arrives at 100%.
4. Percent and bar width should stay in lockstep — no visible lag, no backward motion.
5. Regression: small pulls (1 layer, cached) still complete cleanly.
6. Error path: intentionally break GHCR_TOKEN and pull — bar should freeze at whatever percent was reached, then show ✕ ERROR without resetting width to 0.


